The paper discusses the theory and numerics of compressive sensing, as well as its potential applications and challenges. This suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on signal processing and sparse representations, cs.IT and cs.SP are the most likely categories.
